manently.<br /><br />Good. The second you send me a blacklist, the DMA code gets immediately<br />enabled again. The blacklist doesn't need to be complete - we can fill it<br />up as we hear about more problems (SCSI has had this kind of blacklist for<br />a long time, because even thought the specs clearly specify what a SCSI<br />device should do, there are buggy devices out there that react badly to<br />certain things). <br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br />-<br />To unsubscribe from this list: send the line "unsubscribe linux-kernel" in<br />the body of a message to majordomo&#64;vger.rutgers.edu<br />Please read the FAQ at <a href="http://www.altern.org/andrebalsa/doc/lkml-faq.html">http://www.altern.org/andrebalsa/doc/lkml-faq.html</a><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
